###Global

According to Sina's real-time statistics, as of March 19, as of 8:00, except for China (including Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan regions) , a total of 130132 cases of new crown pneumonia had been confirmed overseas, with 5,446 deaths and 14,378 cured.

0800[ who: 207860 NEW CASES OF PNEUMONIA WORLDWIDE ]

World Health Organization real time statistics show that as of 18:00 central European time (19:01 China Standard Time) , the global cumulative total of new pneumonia confirmed cases of 207860 cases, 8,657 deaths, 166 countries and regions have reported cases.

0800[ who: Some countries still have not reported all cases ]

Ahmad Mandari, director of the WHO's regional office for the eastern Mediterranean, told the meeting that some countries in the region had not yet notified the WHO of all cases. He reiterated the importance of reporting confirmed cases, suspected cases and close contacts of cases to World Health Organization.

###Europe

0800[ add 4,207 confirmed cases to total in Italy ]

As of 18:00 local time on the 18th, Italy 24 hours newly confirmed cases of coronary pneumonia 4207 cases. 35713 cases were diagnosed, 2978 cases died and 4025 cases were cured. Of the 28,710 confirmed cases, 2,257 were critically ill and 12,090 were asymptomatic and isolated at home.

0800[ Spain has confirmed 13,716 cases and declared 20% of GDP as a response to the epidemic ]

There were 2538 newly confirmed cases of coronary pneumonia and 598 deaths. Announcing a $200 billion aid package to ease the impact of the epidemic, which amounts to 20 percent of Spain's gross domestic product, with half of the money going to corporate credit guarantees and the rest to vulnerable groups, it provides benefits to unemployed workers and allows affected groups to suspend mortgage payments.

0800[9,134 confirmed cases of French new coronary pneumonia ]

There were 264 cumulative deaths, and half of the critical patients were under the age of 60. Finance Minister Remere announced a $45 billion fund to "help the French economy and businesses fight the epidemic" and a $300 billion state guarantee for companies to borrow from banks, all measures will also be taken to support big companies, including "nationalisation" .

0800. They're sending a French military plane to pick up a new case of pneumonia

In a televised address, chancellor Merkl said the situation facing Germany was grave and called on all German people to unite to tackle Germany's greatest challenge since the Second World War.

###South America

0800[ Brazilian Senate President and two government ministers confirmed to have new coronavirus infection ]

Brazilian Senate President Eleno and Minister of Mines and Energy Albuquerque have been diagnosed with the new coronavirus, Brazilian officials said Monday, all three are now under house arrest.

0800[ Brazilian stock market remelting ]

###Middle East

The Red Cross Society of China donated a nucleic acid testing laboratory to Iraq, including two PCR machines and 50,000 nucleic acid test kits.
